From 2fca11e3111b623a8a41a524ccf31aef43b75a2e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthew Feickert <matthew.feickert@cern.ch>
Date: Wed, 18 Feb 2026 02:56:46 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] fix: force meson backend for f2py and migrate build.sh to pip
 install
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

f2py on Python 3.11 defaults to the distutils backend, which calls
Compiler.__init__(None, dry_run, force) — a signature incompatible
with the current setuptools Compiler class
(TypeError: takes from 1 to 3 positional arguments but 4 were given).
Explicitly pass --backend meson so f2py uses the meson backend on all
Python versions; meson is provided as a host dependency in the recipe.
---
 pyne/CMakeLists.txt | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/pyne/CMakeLists.txt b/pyne/CMakeLists.txt
index 27670f9a..f28823d8 100644
--- a/pyne/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/pyne/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -74,6 +74,7 @@ if(BUILD_SPATIAL_SOLVER)
             ${F2PY_F90FLAGS}
             --f90flags="-fdefault-real-8"
             --no-wrap-functions
+            --backend meson
             -lpyne
             ${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}/src/transport_spatial_methods/3d/main.f90
     DEPENDS pyne
-- 
